                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14282439" author="hauser@acm.org" created="Mon, 19 Jan 2015 11:59:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;BFO Validator and&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.pdf-tools.com/pdf/pdfa-online-pruefen.aspx&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.pdf-tools.com/pdf/pdfa-online-pruefen.aspx&lt;/a&gt; claim it to be valid&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14282473" author="hauser@acm.org" created="Mon, 19 Jan 2015 13:01:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;as for the 2nd error, too bad, that in the constructor of PDTrueTypeFont, the IOException is only used to falsify the boolean fontIsDamaged and all further hints like &quot;Unexpected end of TTF stream reached&quot; in line 247 of TTFDataStream.java stops after 15 instead of expected 26 characters... are ignored&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14282956" author="jahewson" created="Mon, 19 Jan 2015 20:22:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The idea is that the fontIsDamaged flag only gets set when the font is unreadable. PDF/A doesn&apos;t specify rules for validating font files embedded with PDFs - the details are logged as a warning:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (IOException e)
{
    LOG.warn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Could not read embedded TTF &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; font &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + getBaseFont(), e);
    fontIsDamaged = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt; Looks like you&apos;re seeing a bug in the TTF parser though, which is obviously something we want to fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14282968" author="jahewson" created="Mon, 19 Jan 2015 20:32:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you look in the logs, you&apos;ll find this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;WARNING: Could not read embedded TTF &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; font TJSEEP+Arial-ItalicMT
java.io.IOException: Unexpected end of TTF stream reached
	at org.apache.fontbox.ttf.TTFDataStream.read(TTFDataStream.java:247)
