                            <comment id="14283005" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 19 Jan 2015 21:16:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1653125 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1653125&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1653125&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2608&quot; title=&quot;false negative on pdf/A validation?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2608&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2608&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Don&apos;t read invalid string offsets in TTF name table&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14283006" author="jahewson" created="Mon, 19 Jan 2015 21:17:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This fixes the font reading problem. The font is damaged, it contains invalid offsets in its &apos;name&apos; table. However this doesn&apos;t affect the usefulness of the font, or its validity from a PDF/A perspective.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14283019" author="hauser@acm.org" created="Mon, 19 Jan 2015 21:24:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the apparently ignorable invalid offsets appear to me another candidate for the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2562&quot; title=&quot;create ValidationWarnings&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2562&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2562&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ValidationWarnings&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14283025" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 19 Jan 2015 21:30:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1653127 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1653127&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1653127&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2608&quot; title=&quot;false negative on pdf/A validation?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2608&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2608&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: CR is an end-of-line&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14283027" author="jahewson" created="Mon, 19 Jan 2015 21:31:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This fixes the %%EOF error, which was because Preflight was allowing LR and CRLF but not CR. However, CR on its own is a valid EOL character.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14283041" author="jahewson" created="Mon, 19 Jan 2015 21:36:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe, but fonts which have this problem aren&apos;t really broken - they work fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
